Power supply to areas under the Vyttila Section of the Kerala State Electricity Board like Vyttila-Pettah and nearby roads will be partially regulated between 6 a.m. and 2 p.m. on Sunday; power will be disrupted totally between 6 a.m. and 2 p.m. on Sunday at places along the Pettah-Maradu Road.Power supply to the following places will also be affected on Sunday: Maradu section — Kannadikkadu, Chilavannoor, Chambakkara, Kundannoor, Maradu South and North and areas near Lakeshore Hospital (between 6 a.m. and 1 p.m.); Chottanikkara Section — Irumbanam Puthiya Road, Chithrappuzha, Kollampadi, Hill Palace and Karingachira (between 6 a.m. and 1 p.m.); Tripunithura Section — Pettah, Thamarakulangara, Vadakkekotta, Poornathrayeesa Temple, Statue, S.N. Junction, Old bus stand, Kizhakkekkotta, Nadamapalli, RCM and Chathari (between 6 a.m. and 3 p.m.); and College Section — KPCC Junction, Mullassery Canal Road, Narakathara Road, Shenoy’s Junction and Rajaji Road (between 10.30 a.m. and 5 p.m.). Power supply to places under the Central Section such as Abad Hotel, Kavitha theatre and Doraiswami Iyer Road will be regulated between 2 a.m. and 5.30 p. m. on Monday.